  "prompt": "How easy is it to submit a question on Quora?",
  "response": "Submitting a question on Quora is quite easy. Here\u2019s a simple process to follow:\n\n1. **Sign In/Sign Up**: You need to have a Quora account. You can sign in using your email or social media accounts, or create a new account if you don\u2019t have one.\n  \n2. **Ask a Question**: Once logged in, there\u2019s a prominent \u201cAdd Question\u201d button on the homepage or a text box that says \"What is your question?\" Click on it.\n\n3. **Type Your Question**: Enter your question in the provided text box. Quora may also suggest similar questions as you type.\n\n4. **Format Your Question**: You can add details or context if needed. This can help others provide more accurate answers.\n\n5. **Submit**: After you\u2019re satisfied with your question, you can submit it. You may also have the option to add topics that relate to your question, which helps others find it.\n\n6. **Engagement**: After submission, users can start answering your question, and you can interact with them in the comments or through upvotes.\n\nOverall, the process is straightforward and user-friendly, making it easy for anyone to ask questions on the platform.",
